CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 1, 1954, pg. 21, reads: "NAACP MEMBERSHIP DRIVE OPENS - The 1954 membership campaign of the Pittsburgh Branch of the NAACP opened Sunday at a meeting at Wesley Center AME Zion Church...In the center photo: The Rev. James B. Cayce, campaign chairman, arrives with a load of campaign paraphenalia [sic]... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Rev. James B. Cayce holding box with pamphlets for NAACP membership drive in Wesley Center AME Zion Church
